                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#42r" facs="042"/>
                    The midpoint of the Psalms is marked with a line of alternating red and black dots connected to a small ornamental band. Also, the text <foreign xml:lang="gez">መንፈቅ፡</foreign> ʿhalfʾ
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#77v" facs="078"/>
                    a later hand mentions Wäldä Gäbrǝʾel (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ገብርኤል፡</foreign>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#78r" facs="078"/>
                    a later hand mentions the departed Wäldä Mikaʾel (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ሚካኤል፡</foreign>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#79r" facs="079"/>
                    a later hand mentions Wäldä ʾÄrägawi (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ አረጋዊ፡</foreign>)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#115v" facs="116"> f. 115b, bottom</locus>
                    illegible note
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#28" facs="028"/>
                    white string stitched into fore edge as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#89" facs="089"/>
                    red string stitched into fore edge as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2, 4–6, and 8–10. Quire 10 is marked 20 (<locus target="#68r" facs="068"/>), quire 11 is marked 40 (<locus target="#78r" facs="078"/>). Several quires have numbers on both the first and last folios of the quire
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1r #3r #4r #4v #5r" facs="001 003 004 005"/>, etc.);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#27r #27v #64r #71v #98v" facs="027 028 064 072 099"/>, etc.);
